The paper discusses the stability of auction mechanisms used in sponsored search auctions, which is a topic related to game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also introduces different variants of the Generalized Second Price (GSP) auction that take budgets into account, which involves designing algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The examination of Nash equilibria and envy-free assignments involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
